 GRIGRID 
 ------------------------------------------

GRIGRID is a collection of shell scripts that eases the deployment of combinatorial benchmarks on a cluster.

 REQUIREMENTS
 ------------

- GNU bash, version 4.2.10(1)-release (i386-redhat-linux-gnu)
- GNU Awk 4.0.0
- GNU Octave, version 3.4.3
- Gnuplot 4.4 patchlevel 3
- GNU help2man 1.40.2


 DOCUMENTATION
 -------------

Look for the most up-to-date documentation on the GRIGRID web site, under the documentation menu.
The documentation is also available as manpages.
 

 RELEASE
 -------

A zip archive grigrid-VERSION.tar.gz contains the following directories and files:
- awk/
- bin/ 
- doc/
-octave/
- COPYING
- Makefile
- README

Unzip the archive.
Type `make install' to install the programs and any data files and documentation.
